# Coverage Strategy

## Tool

- **cargo-llvm-cov** -- install once with
  `cargo install cargo-llvm-cov --locked`. Also requires the
  `llvm-tools-preview` rustup component
  (`rustup component add llvm-tools-preview`).

## Threshold

- **Line-coverage threshold: 90%** on all files under `src/model/`.
  Adjust this number explicitly with a one-paragraph rationale if
  the design genuinely cannot reach 90% (e.g. platform-gated code
  paths). Do NOT silently lower the threshold.

## Exclusions

List files / modules excluded from coverage measurement, with a
prose rationale per entry. Exclusions land in the
`--ignore-filename-regex` flag of the run command below
(cargo-llvm-cov accepts a single regex; combine entries with
alternation).

- `src/main.rs` -- `<reason: CLI harness, no model logic>`
- `src/sim.rs` -- `<reason: simulation wrapper, delegates to
  framework>`
- `src/lib.rs` -- `<reason: crate root / module re-exports>`

## Run Command

```bash
# Clears stale profraw + previous report state.
cargo llvm-cov clean --workspace

# Run the full test suite under coverage instrumentation. Uses a
# separate target dir by default so the non-coverage build stays
# clean (no "stale binary" issues across runs).
cargo llvm-cov --workspace --no-report \
  --ignore-filename-regex '(main|sim|lib)\.rs$'

# Emit HTML + LCOV from the same recorded profile data.
cargo llvm-cov report --html --output-dir target/coverage
cargo llvm-cov report --lcov --output-path target/coverage/lcov.info
```

## Report Output

DM3c writes the machine-readable coverage artifact to:

- **LCOV report**: `target/coverage/lcov.info` -- the
  threshold-comparison input the coverage gate consumes.
- **HTML report**: `target/coverage/html/index.html` --
  human-readable dashboard for inspecting uncovered lines.

DM3c records the measured line-coverage percentage and the report
path in `docs/test-plan/test-plan.md`'s `## Coverage` section
once the coverage milestone runs.
